episodes.title: Sex, Pies and Idiot Scrapes
episodes.plot: Homer and Ned go into business together as bounty hunters, and Marge takes a job at an erotic bakery.

episodes.title: Lost Verizon
episodes.plot: Bart gets in trouble with Marge after she finds out that he has Denis Leary's cell phone and is using it to make prank phone calls.

episodes.title: Double, Double, Boy in Trouble
episodes.plot: Bart trades lives with his multi-millionaire lookalike, but discovers that his lookalike's life isn't all he thought it would be.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror XIX
episodes.plot: The Simpsons' 19th Halloween Special, with parodies of "Transformers," "Mad Men," and "It's the Great Pumpkin, Charlie Brown."

episodes.title: Dangerous Curves
episodes.plot: The Simpsons take a Fourth of July vacation to a cabin hotel, which cause Homer and Marge to reminisce about two episodes from their past where they stayed in the cabin.

episodes.title: Homer and Lisa Exchange Cross Words
episodes.plot: Homer gets a job breaking up couples, and Lisa becomes an expert crossword puzzle solver, but Homer bets against her in a competition.

episodes.title: MyPods and Boomsticks
episodes.plot: Homer suspects that the family of Bart's new Muslim friend from Jordan is part of a terrorist plot, and Lisa becomes obsessed with her new MyPod.

episodes.title: The Burns and the Bees
episodes.plot: Mr. Burns wins a professional basketball team in a poker game, and the new arena he plans to have Springfield build for the team threatens to interfere with Lisa's new bee sanctuary.

episodes.title: Lisa the Drama Queen
episodes.plot: Lisa and her new best friend create their own fantasy world, but Marge doesn't want Lisa to see her friend anymore after she finds out that they're too far gone in it.

episodes.title: Take My Life, Please
episodes.plot: Homer finds out that he actually won the senior class president election, and he gets an opportunity to find out how his life would have been different if it had happened.

episodes.title: How the Test Was Won
episodes.plot: Bart and his fellow underachievers are taken on a "field trip" to Capital City so that they can miss the standardized test, and Homer makes sure that nothing bad happens until their insurance goes back into effect.

episodes.title: No Loan Again, Naturally
episodes.plot: The Simpsons lose their house, but Flanders buys it and offers to rent it back to them. But when they turn out to be less-than-reliable renters, Flanders kicks them out.

episodes.title: Gone Maggie Gone
episodes.plot: In order to rescue Maggie from a Catholic orphanage, Lisa must solve a series of puzzles to reveal the identity of a gem that will bring peace to Springfield.

episodes.title: In the Name of the Grandfather
episodes.plot: The Simpsons take Grandpa to Ireland so he can go back to visit a pub he went to during the war, but Grandpa and Homer get suckered into buying the bar.

episodes.title: Wedding for Disaster
episodes.plot: Homer is kidnapped moments before he and Marge are supposed to re-renew their vows. However, Marge comes to the conclusion that Homer left her at the altar.

episodes.title: Eeny Teeny Maya Moe
episodes.plot: Moe begins dating a little person he met on the Internet, while Maggie is being bullied at the playground next to Moe's where Homer is leaving her.

episodes.title: The Good, the Sad and the Drugly
episodes.plot: Bart gets Milhouse to take the rap for a prank at school, and then blows him off when he falls for a cute 5th grade do-gooder, prompting Milhouse's wrath. Meanwhile, Lisa begins taking "happy pills" to improve her negative outlook.

episodes.title: Father Knows Worst
episodes.plot: Homer becomes a "helicopter parent" at Springfield Elementary by helping Bart finish a class project and helping Lisa become popular, and Marge finds a secret sauna in their house.

episodes.title: Waverly Hills, 9021-D'Oh
episodes.plot: The Simpsons set up a fake residence in Waverly Hills so that Bart and Lisa can attend school there.

episodes.title: Four Great Women and a Manicure
episodes.plot: A series of parodies based on four strong women: Queen Elizabeth, Snow White, Lady MacBeth, and Ayn Rand.

episodes.title: Coming to Homerica
episodes.plot: Townspeople build a wall around Springfield to keep "immigrants" from Ogdenville from relocating to their town.
